Adjusted Automotive Free Cash Flow We measure adjusted automotive free cash flow as automotive operating cash flow from
operations less capital expenditures adjusted for management actions. For the year ended December 31, 2021, net automotive cash
provided by operating activities under U.S. GAAP was $9.7 billion, capital expenditures were $7.4 billion and adjustments for
management actions were $0.3 billion. For the year ended December 31, 2020, net automotive cash provided by operating activities
under U.S. GAAP was $7.5 billion, capital expenditures were $5.3 billion and adjustments for management actions were $0.3
billion.
