Other Remeasurements The SOA issued mortality improvement tables in the three months ended December 31, 2021 and
December 31, 2020. We reviewed our recent mortality experience and we determined our current mortality assumptions are
appropriate to measure our U.S. pension and OPEB plans obligations as of December 31, 2021. In 2020, we incorporated the SOA
mortality improvement tables into our December 31, 2020 measurement of U.S. pension and OPEB plans' benefit obligations. The
change in these assumptions decreased U.S. pension and OPEB plans’ obligations by $686 million as of December 31, 2020.
